  "response": "Yes, Ryan Gosling is considered a good singer. He has showcased his vocal talents in several films and musical projects. Some notable examples include:\n\n1. **\"La La Land\" (2016)**: Gosling played the role of Sebastian, a jazz pianist and aspiring club owner, in this musical film. He performed several songs, including \"City of Stars,\" which won the Academy Award for Best Original Song.\n\n2. **\"The Notebook\" (2004)**: Although not a musical, Gosling's character, Noah, sings a short rendition of \"I'll Be Seeing You\" in the film.\n\n3. **\"Blue Valentine\" (2010)**: Gosling performed a ukulele version of \"You Always Hurt the One You Love\" in this drama.\n\n4. **\"Dead Man's Bones\"**: Gosling is also part of a musical duo called Dead Man's Bones, where he sings and plays various instruments. The band\u2019s self-titled album, released in 2009, blends elements of indie rock and orchestral music.\n\nWhile Gosling may not be a professional singer by trade, his performances have been well-received, and he has demonstrated a credible and enjoyable singing ability in his various roles and projects.",
